le do run 3 but I really find that it would be useless in most situations unless you are a puller indoors. I do pull but a regularly over camped Velk has really made me hate pulling, still like places in Chardok though.<br><br>What I have been recomending to my tank friends is put points into regen first since that WILL help lower mana comsumption on the healer.<br><br>To get your 6 points to move on to Archtype skills you may want to add run 3 after regen but then I really see no merit in others except maybe agility, stamina or resists.<br><br>In archtype I plan on going for combat furry for some crits and I believe fear resistance lies in there. I'm doubting the usefullness of perma fearless at 60 though. Basically anything to up my damage output would be nice since I do solo at times.<br><br>I'm not sure if I really want the horse but a friend in my guild got it and loves that it walks at SoW speed and you don't have to sit to med you just stop running and fighting.<br><br>Any ideas about the top end skills? <p><center><image src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jayrj1/Fironasig.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/22/02 1:45:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I put my AA points in?</span><hr size=1> I can make a comment in regards to fearless.<br><br>Initially when I saw the first list of AA skills, I thought fearless would be so superb. But the skill seems to have little use at the time you get it.<br><br>Couple days ago we fought Gore, put semi-light MR gear on, maybe 100MR unbuffed. Did not get feared once with GRM and aoe bard song going. <br><br>Outside of Kunark dragons nothing really has a strong fear wh en you are 60. So not really worth sinking the arch skill points into it.<br><br>Surpsingly I found enough time to grind to class skills and have the choice shortly. Each class skills naturally differs in usefullness a lot depending on your play style.<br><br>For solo/grinding(you as the tank) double riposte gives 1% more damage output for each level trained. Slay undead 3 increases you meele output by about 19%. Bash gives you about 1% more damage.<br><br>I tend to grind little and my role on raid is predominatly AoE healer with very decent damage output at the same time. So I put points into healing adept/gift to increase my healing a tad from FM to oom. <br><br>For class skills I will go for horse first just to speed up travel time. Then I will raise either HPs with ND2&amp;3 or CF 2&amp;3 if I want to go the undead route. But with my little grind time, 19 points to get to slay undead 3 is just way too long for me =p We'll see.<br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubanyon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banyon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/23/02 10:08:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.seacove.net/ccbbc/images/kokopeli.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I put my AA points in?</span><hr size=1> Kron,<br><br>Rather than STA 3, I suggest Regen 3<br><br>Reason is:<br>At level 60, 1 STA = 4 HP  3 STA = 12 HP.<br>Regen 3 = 3 HP regened every 6 secs.  <br><br>Average fight at the lvl 55 - 60 game is (for this example) one minute.<br>In one min:<br>3 STA = 12 HP<br>3 Regen = 30 HP<br><br>While STA looks nice, Regen is (IMHO) the way to go to mitigate / offset the damage that you take.<br><br>Just my 2cp  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><hr><center><table> <TR><td></td>  <TD>- <A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6762>Banyon</a><br>- 59 Troubadour<br>- Officer, <A HREF=http://www.eqdragoncouncil.org>Dragon Council</a><br></td><TD></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeentrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geen Trueblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/24/02 3:43:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I put my AA points in?</span><hr size=1> He would get 2 stam per aa point so thats 24hp instead of 12 and 40 if he maxed it. But I agree about going regen first. I think regen &gt; runspeed unless you pull alot. Ill still go for 3 in run speed after regen though, because it does have uses outdoors as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><