sow gets dispelled. You can avoid any hits while running back from pull. (I pull with spell to have distance but you still have times where you run into an add or cannot get to a mob with a spell before getting hit). And if you crowd control on a pull of multiples, then you can do so without getting hit too.<br><br>You can swim backwards in kedge or any other underwater place.<br><br>/shrug, I do not understand the discussion =)<br><br>For the sta debate:<br><br>- 1 sta is around 5.2 HP for a paladin at 60<br>- improved stamina = 10.4 HP per AA point<br>- natural durability I is 40HP+, 20 HP per AA point<br>- natural durability II is 60HP+, 16 HP per AA point<br>- natural durability III is 100HP+, 16 HP per AA point<br><br>So if you want to go max HP, place 3 in improve stamina, then go full ND, then back to stamina.<br><br><br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usasmina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sasmina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 6:41:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I put my AA points in?</span><hr size=1> <br>First I agreee with Senchy on his comment- Resistant to fear is Nice but when u really need it vs Dragons then Hopefully you have the bards and you Resist gear in order.<br><br>I Can tell you what I have used my AA point to so far<br><br>3 points into running speed (its really good in dungeons)<br>3 points into Wisdom (I need it badly - I am play Human)<br><br>Arch AA<b