d 3<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Package B: (41 points)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Durability, Stability, Agility 1<br>PE<br>Durability, Stability, Agility 3<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Package C: (5 points)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Holy Steed<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Package D: (6 points)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Improved LoH<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Package E: (5 points)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>2H Bash<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Package F: (41 points)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Spell Reinforcement 3<br>Mental Clarity 3<br>Nat Regen 3<br>Body and Mind<br><br>These are the basics in my mind. The other skills are less useful. Some of these packages (especially F), it can make sense to just buy the first part of them, while others (like A), it only makes sense to go for them if you going all the way to the end.<br><br>If you raid with your guild a lot on undead mobs, or if you can gain exp on undead mobs, then I would go with Package A as soon as possible. With Slay Undead 3, I do monk or wizard damage on mobs, equal to the lesser rogues (but a significant bit under the top couple rogues), but still almost double the warriors and the like. (On one mob, the warriors were around 12k each, I was about 25k, the best rogues were over 30k). Slay undead also has the best fun factor of any skill we have.<br><br>You want to go with package B if you find yourself tanking a lot of mobs, be it soloing, or raiding. If healing/mana is never an issue, then package B doesnt give you a big win, because you dont kill mobs any faster when doing exp. Similarly, if you never tank, not even adds on raids or rampage, then Package B doesnt give you a lot. If you do these things, then it is a big win.<br><br>Package C (Holy Steed) is a big win when you are traveling. You just get around TONS faster. It has some other advantages, but the big win here is you can get around REALLY fast. It also has a big fun factor, second only to slay undead imho.<br><br>Package D (Improved LoH) is a win for whenever you use LoH. This makes LoH when soloing a true get out of jail free card (especially if you usually solo with long duration buffs like Aego). Without this skill, a LoH was about a 50% heal, making it not very useful at all. It also is a huge win on raids. If your LoH use is important a lot on raids, then go for this skill, because it will make your LoH be a 6000pt heal on a main tank, rather than the rather mediocre 2300ish heal it was.<br><br>Package E (2h Bash) is a win if you use a 2h weapon and find yourself wanting to interrupt casters. This is mainly useful when soloing, as any caster that bash would interrupt is going to die too fast to get any important spell off in a raid situation anyway.<br><br>Package F is mainly geared for those who solo a lot using CC, or perhaps use it a lot in a raid (why?). If you truely solo (not using a heal bot), and cast CC a lot, then spell casting reinforcment will make your heals much more effective. The additional mana regen and healing regen will also help the true soloer.<br><br>Personally, for the all round general lvl 60 paladin, I would recommend going A, C, D, B, E, F in that order. Going A first will just let you get exp so much faster and is so much fun you really should do it first unless you are the atypical paladin (ie, if you are a 60 paladin that always and only hunts with the same group of 5 people, and you are always the tank, then go with B first).<br><br>-Iustus <p><BR>Duke Iustus <BR>Crusader of Marr <BR>Tarew Marr<BR><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiustus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iustus</A> at: 3/13/02 12:08:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" 