/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I am sure I must be missing something (since I have heard run ingame also, hehe), but run does not appeal to me all that much. I understand that it does not stack with any run speed buffs, so is only really relevant for dungeons or as insurance against dispells while pulling. I was never a puller on raids, so do not have to worry about dispells, and I never had any problem pulling in dungeon exp groups with my plain old running speed.<br><br>On the other hand, I have always regretted that I made Marlowe a wisdom challenged half elf (he was my first character and I was indeed EQ ignorant), especially, since I often served as a healer during my career. Yes, I carry alt gear that, with buffs, allows me to break 200 wisdom (at the cost of horrendous AC), but I would not mind some extra mana when wearing more typical gear (with wisdom only in the 110-120 range). Given this, would wisdom be an awful choice for my initial AA points? <p>Marlowe Lawbringer<BR>Crusader of Mithaniel Marr, Level 60 (Retired)<BR>Innoruuk<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhyprionthecrusader.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyprion The Crusader</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 11:59:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I put my AA points in?</span><hr size=1> Its totally a matter of personal taste and your playstyle what you want to do with them. If you like tanking a lot or if you are in situations where you take lots of AE damage or rampages, then getting Natural durability, combat agility and stability would be best for you. Most pallys go the crits/slay undead route though. I have fury2, but I dont plan on getting slay undead any time soon, I dont care about dealing damage as much as taking it. I also heal a lot on raids so healing gift is nice. <br><br>Atm I have run3, stam3, durability3, fury2 and healing gift1, my next points will go to Agility, Holy Steed and Improved Lay Hands. Then I will prolly do Physical Enhancement and some mental clarity.. havent decided yet.<br><br>Im a HP freak though ...to each his own...have fun with it ther is no *right* way to do it.  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4342 target="_blank"><img src=http://www.prowlerz.net/alarie/hyp20.jpg border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushnarsty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shnarsty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 3:44:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I put my AA points in?</span><hr size=1> I spread my points around pretty well so far.  I'm happy with what I have done for the most part.<br><br>Here's the path I took:<br><br>General:<br>1 run<br>5 stamina<br><br>Archetype:<br>natural durability 1<br>combat fury 1<br>combat stability 1<br>combat agility 1<br>natural durability 2<br><br>Class:<br>Holy Steed<br><br>then I went back to archetype and got:<br>natural durability 3<br>Combat fury 3<br><br>I am now 1 point away from slay undead 1, and I am gonna keep grinding till I get it.<br><br>Natural Durability 3 is my favorite of these skills.  I got up to 5500 hps raid buffed and I dont even have any CT/NToV loots. <p><Br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45641" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.pet